Characters, actions, places, occupations, and events in this series

2
00:00:07,940 --> 00:00:10,980
are fictional and created for entertainment purposes only.

3
00:00:11,000 --> 00:00:15,820
They are not intended to urge or promote any behavior in the series.

4
00:00:15,840 --> 00:00:18,460
Viewer discretion is advised.

5
00:00:19,650 --> 00:00:22,080
The power of the Golden Blood is too almighty.

6
00:00:22,110 --> 00:00:25,230
We can’t let the Golden Blood fall into Nakan’s hand.

7
00:00:26,610 --> 00:00:28,560
Until you turn 21.

8
00:00:29,140 --> 00:00:31,200
I will be taking care of you all the time.

9
00:00:32,110 --> 00:00:33,400
Starting now.

10
00:00:35,400 --> 00:00:38,850
I heard you said you have the special blood

11
00:00:38,880 --> 00:00:40,180
wanted by the vampires?

12
00:00:44,260 --> 00:00:44,770
Stop!

13
00:00:49,600 --> 00:00:50,180
Mister!

14
00:00:50,790 --> 00:00:52,210
Didn’t you say you are immortal?

15
00:00:52,260 --> 00:00:53,190
Mister!

16
00:00:57,020 --> 00:00:58,420
Your wounds are gone.

17
00:00:58,960 --> 00:01:00,340
You smell so nice.

18
00:02:28,020 --> 00:02:29,660
Are you sure

19
00:02:29,690 --> 00:02:31,060
you want to live here with me?

20
00:02:38,950 --> 00:02:40,950
It's because of the Golden Blood, isn't it?

21
00:02:41,810 --> 00:02:43,540
That's why people got dragged into trouble.

22
00:02:47,170 --> 00:02:49,300
I don't want anyone to get into trouble because of me anymore.

23
00:02:55,250 --> 00:02:56,550
I'll live with you

24
00:02:57,570 --> 00:02:58,870
until I turn 21.

25
00:03:10,510 --> 00:03:11,620
Hello, Kla.

26
00:03:12,130 --> 00:03:12,780
Yeah

27
00:03:14,770 --> 00:03:15,920
I have something to tell you.

28
00:03:17,920 --> 00:03:19,400
I got a scholarship.

29
00:03:20,380 --> 00:03:21,250
Yeah.

30
00:03:22,950 --> 00:03:25,110
The thing is, my advisor gave me a scholarship

31
00:03:25,120 --> 00:03:26,770
in return for me helping out with the research.

32
00:03:29,520 --> 00:03:32,030
I have to move into the school's accommodation
and I have to move in tonight.

33
00:03:34,800 --> 00:03:36,180
I told Miss Nuan already.

34
00:03:36,700 --> 00:03:37,810
She gave me permission.

35
00:03:40,530 --> 00:03:42,350
Yeah, don't worry about me.

36
00:03:43,050 --> 00:03:44,990
Hey, Kla.

37
00:03:45,020 --> 00:03:46,070
I have to go now.

38
00:03:46,590 --> 00:03:47,530
I'll talk to you later.

39
00:03:47,550 --> 00:03:48,350
Alright.

40
00:04:13,760 --> 00:04:14,660
Hold on.

41
00:04:21,300 --> 00:04:24,160
No one else is living here, right?

42
00:04:24,660 --> 00:04:27,270
No, I live here alone.

43
00:04:28,440 --> 00:04:29,460
Wait, wait.

44
00:04:31,460 --> 00:04:34,470
There's nothing strange, right?

45
00:04:35,200 --> 00:04:38,159
What do you mean by ”strange”?

46
00:04:39,250 --> 00:04:40,880
A coffin in the middle of the house

47
00:04:40,900 --> 00:04:42,030
something like that.

48
00:04:43,300 --> 00:04:44,320
Come in and see for yourself.

49
00:04:54,180 --> 00:04:55,590
Is it like what you imagined?

50
00:04:58,750 --> 00:05:01,330
Well, it's not like what I had in mind.

51
00:05:01,860 --> 00:05:05,140
The vampires' tricks worked beyond expectations.

52
00:05:05,180 --> 00:05:10,320
You might have thought we still live in a dark castle

53
00:05:10,350 --> 00:05:11,910
or sleep in a coffin.

54
00:05:12,190 --> 00:05:17,650
Like, in the haunted houses?

55
00:05:17,920 --> 00:05:19,170
Something along that line.

56
00:05:19,200 --> 00:05:20,530
Think about it,

57
00:05:21,180 --> 00:05:23,890
if we still live in such a dark castle,

58
00:05:24,420 --> 00:05:27,710
you guys would have visited it as if it's a landmark.

59
00:05:28,540 --> 00:05:30,140
Humans learn to adapt.

60
00:05:30,970 --> 00:05:32,210
So do we.

61
00:05:33,290 --> 00:05:34,930
But there's a room

62
00:05:35,920 --> 00:05:38,659
that no matter how long the time has passed,

63
00:05:38,680 --> 00:05:39,730
it’s still a necessity.

64
00:05:40,640 --> 00:05:41,670
What room?

65
00:05:42,960 --> 00:05:44,370
The tribute room.

66
00:05:48,550 --> 00:05:49,650
Follow me.

67
00:05:57,070 --> 00:05:58,440
Is there really such a room?

68
00:06:14,440 --> 00:06:16,830
I had someone move all your stuff in already.

69
00:06:17,460 --> 00:06:21,020
Both a vampire and a bellboy?

70
00:06:21,060 --> 00:06:22,440
You're stretching them thin.

71
00:06:32,880 --> 00:06:36,840
Where are you going to sleep?

72
00:06:37,200 --> 00:06:39,570
You're not going to watch me around the clock, are you?

73
00:06:40,050 --> 00:06:41,020
What do you think?

74
00:06:41,800 --> 00:06:42,580
Mister.

75
00:06:44,170 --> 00:06:48,850
The bed is too small for two big men.

76
00:06:49,240 --> 00:06:50,780
I won't take your bed.

77
00:06:51,550 --> 00:06:53,140
This entire room is yours.

78
00:06:54,050 --> 00:06:56,190
Since we're going to live together,

79
00:06:56,210 --> 00:06:57,990
you should know this, Tong.

80
00:06:58,020 --> 00:07:00,850
Vampires don't need sleep.

81
00:07:01,370 --> 00:07:02,490
What do you mean?

82
00:07:02,880 --> 00:07:06,140
It means that I can watch over you around the clock.

83
00:07:11,570 --> 00:07:13,350
Are you sure you're going to just watch over me?

84
00:07:14,020 --> 00:07:17,990
Don't you sneak in and suck my blood while I'm sleeping.

85
00:07:18,450 --> 00:07:19,980
Why would I do that?

86
00:07:20,200 --> 00:07:21,620
If I really want to drink your blood,

87
00:07:23,510 --> 00:07:24,840
I can do that anytime.

88
00:07:42,210 --> 00:07:43,540
You smell so nice.

89
00:08:07,580 --> 00:08:08,450
Okay?

90
00:08:11,280 --> 00:08:13,280
Then leave already.

91
00:08:40,429 --> 00:08:41,669
Where's my guitar?

92
00:08:42,260 --> 00:08:43,110
Hey!

93
00:08:44,820 --> 00:08:46,100
Why are you here again?

94
00:08:46,540 --> 00:08:48,100
To give you your guitar.

95
00:08:48,660 --> 00:08:49,320
Here.

96
00:08:58,030 --> 00:08:58,820
Hey!

97
00:09:00,210 --> 00:09:01,730
From now on,

98
00:09:01,760 --> 00:09:03,550
don't come any closer than this.

99
00:09:03,580 --> 00:09:04,810
One arm's length.

100
00:09:07,080 --> 00:09:08,520
Your arm or my arm?

101
00:09:09,070 --> 00:09:10,930
Our arms are not the same length.

102
00:09:12,350 --> 00:09:14,790
It doesn't matter whose arm it is.

103
00:09:16,290 --> 00:09:20,060
Also, don't enter at your own will from now on.

104
00:09:20,580 --> 00:09:22,900
No sneaking up on me too.

105
00:09:30,270 --> 00:09:31,490
Did you get that?

106
00:09:31,840 --> 00:09:32,530
Hey!

107
00:09:32,840 --> 00:09:33,920
Answer me!

108
00:09:33,940 --> 00:09:34,790
Hey!

109
00:09:55,120 --> 00:09:57,010
(Pull yourself together, Tong.)

110
00:09:57,820 --> 00:09:59,390
(Keep your guard up all the time)

111
00:10:00,080 --> 00:10:01,070
(because that vampire)

112
00:10:01,120 --> 00:10:02,970
(can eat you up anytime.)

113
00:10:03,010 --> 00:10:04,720
(Can't be trusted at all costs!)

114
00:13:06,820 --> 00:13:08,720
Didn't he say he wouldn't come in?

115
00:13:36,390 --> 00:13:37,330
Are you hungry yet?

116
00:13:39,090 --> 00:13:41,430
Don't you only drink tomato juice?

117
00:13:42,610 --> 00:13:44,070
This is all for you.

118
00:13:44,100 --> 00:13:44,920
What?

119
00:13:46,140 --> 00:13:46,930
For me?

120
00:13:46,960 --> 00:13:48,350
All these?

121
00:13:50,500 --> 00:13:53,130
I wanted you to try new thing

122
00:13:53,520 --> 00:13:54,900
so I ordered different sorts of things.

123
00:13:55,200 --> 00:13:59,860
You're not trying to fatten me up and eat me later, are you?

124
00:14:03,860 --> 00:14:06,120
I don't know which place has good food.

125
00:14:06,160 --> 00:14:08,450
So I ordered from ones with good reviews

126
00:14:08,480 --> 00:14:10,210
or got a Michelin Star.

127
00:14:10,820 --> 00:14:12,210
For some,

128
00:14:12,240 --> 00:14:14,210
I even had to jump the queue for you.

129
00:14:15,540 --> 00:14:18,500
I just wanted you to know
that I will take great care of you.

130
00:14:30,000 --> 00:14:32,000
Good morning, Mr. Tong.

131
00:14:33,520 --> 00:14:35,410
Would you like some coffee or tea?

132
00:14:35,610 --> 00:14:38,230
Uh, it's alright.

133
00:14:38,630 --> 00:14:41,170
Or would you like some tomato juice like Mr. Mark?

134
00:14:41,910 --> 00:14:44,540
I'll just have water.

135
00:15:11,570 --> 00:15:12,720
Wow!

136
00:15:13,150 --> 00:15:13,940
Mister!

137
00:15:14,890 --> 00:15:16,570
This is so delicious.

138
00:15:17,890 --> 00:15:19,090
Is it that good?

139
00:15:20,140 --> 00:15:21,070
Aren't you going to eat?

140
00:15:21,360 --> 00:15:22,950
We don't need food.

141
00:15:24,000 --> 00:15:24,820
Mister!

142
00:15:25,590 --> 00:15:26,830
This is bomb!

143
00:15:26,870 --> 00:15:28,460
So good!

144
00:15:30,310 --> 00:15:31,530
What a shame

145
00:15:32,260 --> 00:15:33,560
that you’re a vampire.

146
00:15:35,100 --> 00:15:36,360
You have money

147
00:15:36,570 --> 00:15:38,690
but no chance to enjoy delicious foods like these.

148
00:15:57,890 --> 00:15:58,890
Have you changed your mind?

149
00:16:04,890 --> 00:16:06,020
Want some?

150
00:16:18,020 --> 00:16:18,880
How was it?

151
00:16:18,900 --> 00:16:20,030
Delicious, right?

152
00:16:43,110 --> 00:16:47,420
Since you're the host of this house and this meal,

153
00:16:48,500 --> 00:16:49,810
I'll give you this dish.

154
00:16:50,310 --> 00:16:50,780
Alright?

155
00:16:53,090 --> 00:16:53,940
Here.

156
00:17:33,520 --> 00:17:34,450
Mister.

157
00:17:34,940 --> 00:17:36,840
Have you got anything for me to do?

158
00:17:36,890 --> 00:17:38,290
I don't want to sit here doing nothing.

159
00:17:39,280 --> 00:17:41,000
When I was at the orphanage,

160
00:17:41,030 --> 00:17:43,240
Miss Nuan told us that we have to have our duty

161
00:17:43,280 --> 00:17:44,550
and be helpful.

162
00:17:47,160 --> 00:17:47,910
Mister.

163
00:17:49,660 --> 00:17:51,040
Is there a mall around here?

164
00:17:51,090 --> 00:17:52,690
I want to buy some stuff.

165
00:17:53,570 --> 00:17:55,630
Just tell me what you want.

166
00:17:55,680 --> 00:17:56,840
I'll get them for you.

167
00:17:58,300 --> 00:17:59,860
It's my clothes.

168
00:17:59,880 --> 00:18:01,780
How can I have someone buy it in my stead?

169
00:18:01,830 --> 00:18:03,080
Do you know my size?

170
00:18:16,410 --> 00:18:17,170
Get up.

171
00:18:20,180 --> 00:18:21,020
Hey, hey!

172
00:18:22,210 --> 00:18:23,140
What are you doing?

173
00:18:24,850 --> 00:18:25,930
One arm's length.

174
00:18:32,520 --> 00:18:33,780
22.

175
00:18:36,220 --> 00:18:38,270
Hey, what are you doing?

176
00:18:39,140 --> 00:18:40,770
I'm measuring out your size.

177
00:18:40,800 --> 00:18:41,910
Stay still.

178
00:18:48,030 --> 00:18:49,650
31.5.

179
00:18:50,720 --> 00:18:51,710
Give me your arms.

180
00:18:55,780 --> 00:18:57,000
39.

181
00:19:04,220 --> 00:19:05,090
19.

182
00:19:14,150 --> 00:19:15,260
Now I know

183
00:19:15,770 --> 00:19:17,650
that all your measurements

184
00:19:18,280 --> 00:19:20,040
are one size smaller than mine.

185
00:19:22,720 --> 00:19:24,830
How do you know that it applies to 'all' my measurements?

186
00:19:25,840 --> 00:19:27,250
Isn't it obvious?

187
00:19:33,150 --> 00:19:34,540
Tell me if you need anything,

188
00:19:34,580 --> 00:19:35,520
got it?

189
00:19:37,520 --> 00:19:38,290
Yeah.

190
00:19:51,740 --> 00:19:53,760
Are you just going to stand there and watch?

191
00:19:54,630 --> 00:19:55,990
Don't you want to take on anything?

192
00:19:56,850 --> 00:19:57,790
Nah.

193
00:19:57,820 --> 00:19:59,790
I'm bored so I'm just looking around.

194
00:20:02,110 --> 00:20:03,750
Did you find anything interesting?

195
00:20:04,950 --> 00:20:06,810
There is quite something.

196
00:20:07,610 --> 00:20:09,200
I'll try it out.

197
00:20:24,640 --> 00:20:27,120
You've never tried weight training before, have you?

198
00:20:29,170 --> 00:20:29,940
No.

199
00:20:29,970 --> 00:20:31,090
I'll teach you.

200
00:20:32,050 --> 00:20:33,490
If you do it alone,
You might injure yourself

201
00:20:40,170 --> 00:20:41,170
Like this?

202
00:20:41,920 --> 00:20:43,070
This is for your shoulder.

203
00:20:44,030 --> 00:20:46,460
Lift them up and breathe out.

204
00:21:05,510 --> 00:21:06,340
Hey!

205
00:21:06,370 --> 00:21:07,070
Mister!

206
00:21:07,700 --> 00:21:09,020
Aren't you going to save me anymore?

207
00:22:07,890 --> 00:22:08,530
Mister.

208
00:22:09,180 --> 00:22:10,450
Aren't you going to run anymore?

209
00:22:16,000 --> 00:22:18,150
I'm bothering you too much, am I?

210
00:22:21,980 --> 00:22:23,090
I'm sorry.

211
00:23:07,810 --> 00:23:08,880
I…

212
00:23:08,930 --> 00:23:10,450
forgot my slippers.

213
00:23:17,670 --> 00:23:20,050
Next time, put your towel away after using it.

214
00:23:45,360 --> 00:23:46,930
Oh, Mister!

215
00:23:49,450 --> 00:23:51,260
You have to go to work?

216
00:23:52,010 --> 00:23:53,650
I have to go to the medical center.

217
00:23:54,200 --> 00:23:56,040
There's some work I have to take care of.

218
00:23:57,090 --> 00:23:58,930
You can take care of yourself, right?

219
00:24:03,250 --> 00:24:04,100
Yeah.

220
00:24:05,490 --> 00:24:07,490
Actually, Aunty Wan is also not here today.

221
00:24:08,010 --> 00:24:10,960
It's quite dangerous to leave you here alone.

222
00:24:13,350 --> 00:24:14,500
Would you like to come with me?

223
00:24:17,190 --> 00:24:18,450
Really?

224
00:24:18,480 --> 00:24:19,530
Can I really come along?

225
00:24:20,410 --> 00:24:23,860
But you might have to be closer to me than one arm's length.

226
00:24:24,520 --> 00:24:25,780
Is that okay with you?

227
00:24:28,910 --> 00:24:30,610
I'll let you get away with it for a day.

228
00:24:33,020 --> 00:24:33,800
Then,

229
00:24:33,840 --> 00:24:35,630
I'll get changed first.

230
00:25:06,590 --> 00:25:07,320
Tong.

231
00:25:08,260 --> 00:25:09,490
Come and walk beside me.

232
00:25:12,380 --> 00:25:13,120
Let's go.

233
00:25:20,640 --> 00:25:23,600
Mr. Mark, Miss Thara is waiting to see you.

234
00:25:24,040 --> 00:25:25,730
Wait for me at the coffee shop.

235
00:25:25,750 --> 00:25:26,900
Mr. Tong as well.

236
00:25:26,930 --> 00:25:29,440
Miss Thara would like to meet both of you.

237
00:25:29,970 --> 00:25:30,940
Mr. Tong too?

238
00:25:30,970 --> 00:25:33,960
Yes, Miss Thara is already aware that Mr. Tong is here too.

239
00:25:34,900 --> 00:25:35,880
This way, please.

240
00:26:07,490 --> 00:26:09,490
It's nice to finally meet you, Tong.

241
00:26:11,490 --> 00:26:12,240
Hello.

242
00:26:12,270 --> 00:26:13,330
Hello.

243
00:26:15,190 --> 00:26:16,700
Can I have your hands?

244
00:26:19,190 --> 00:26:20,070
My hands?

245
00:26:37,580 --> 00:26:39,010
If I were you,

246
00:26:40,980 --> 00:26:42,840
if there were a staring portrait beside my bed,

247
00:26:42,880 --> 00:26:44,840
I would have covered it up with something too.

248
00:26:46,240 --> 00:26:47,440
You could see it?

249
00:26:49,970 --> 00:26:51,380
Thank you so much, Tong.

250
00:26:53,540 --> 00:26:55,860
It couldn't have been easy all these times, was it?

251
00:26:56,440 --> 00:26:58,440
Both at the orphanage and here.

252
00:26:59,460 --> 00:27:01,460
It wasn't too bad.

253
00:27:02,790 --> 00:27:06,140
Miss Nuan took great care of me.

254
00:27:07,320 --> 00:27:09,020
Hang in there just a little more, Tong.

255
00:27:10,560 --> 00:27:12,370
When the Golden Blood appears.

256
00:27:13,490 --> 00:27:15,260
When the moon hangs low.

257
00:27:19,100 --> 00:27:20,510
That's when peace

258
00:27:21,490 --> 00:27:22,580
shall return.

259
00:27:32,100 --> 00:27:33,510
Has Mark been taking good care of you?

260
00:27:36,170 --> 00:27:37,840
Did he put you in a hard place?

261
00:27:38,320 --> 00:27:40,710
Or if he ever bothers you,
just let me know,

262
00:27:40,740 --> 00:27:42,140
I'll handle Mark for you.

263
00:27:42,610 --> 00:27:43,650
I can do that?

264
00:27:43,680 --> 00:27:44,780
Of course.

265
00:27:48,870 --> 00:27:51,730
Then if Mr. Mark ever bothered me again,

266
00:27:52,400 --> 00:27:54,140
I'll tell you right away.

267
00:27:58,560 --> 00:27:59,900
Thank you so much, Tong.

268
00:28:01,840 --> 00:28:04,720
You might not know how important you are to us.

269
00:28:07,090 --> 00:28:08,500
And I'm sorry

270
00:28:09,650 --> 00:28:12,380
for making you get involved with the vampires like this.

271
00:28:19,790 --> 00:28:22,460
That boy has a kind heart.

272
00:28:23,410 --> 00:28:26,320
I haven't met anyone with such a kind heart like his in a long time.

273
00:28:27,920 --> 00:28:28,610
Yes.

274
00:28:30,770 --> 00:28:33,270
But it's someone with a kind heart like Tong

275
00:28:33,300 --> 00:28:34,720
who is the weakest.

276
00:28:35,810 --> 00:28:39,250
Because a kind heart is prone to shatter.

277
00:28:40,710 --> 00:28:43,570
Even though he has the most powerful blood?

278
00:28:45,740 --> 00:28:48,800
You realize the power of the Golden Blood firsthand

279
00:28:49,640 --> 00:28:51,740
because you have drunk Tong's blood, is that right?

280
00:28:59,940 --> 00:29:01,000
My apologies.

281
00:29:02,130 --> 00:29:04,130
I didn't mean for it to happen.

282
00:29:05,660 --> 00:29:07,570
I've seen it in the vision already.

283
00:29:08,840 --> 00:29:11,890
